er languages.","French: habitational name from Gray in Haute-Saône or Le Gray in Seine-Maritime."]},{"name":"Greiwe","meanings":["German: possibly a nickname from Middle High German <i>greibe</i> ‘sharp, tangy, dour’. Compare   Grey  ."]}]},{"name":"Marjory","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual modern spelling of   Margery .  It seems to have arisen as the result of folk etymological association of the name with that of the herb <i>marjoram</i> (  compare  Rosemary  ). This word is of uncertain origin; its Middle English and Old French form was <i>majorane</i>, without the first <i>-r-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Marjory Grey was born in 1254, in Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Sir Patrick Ogilvey. She died in 1300, in her hometown, at the age of 46."},"et":{"1254–1300":"1254–1300","1252–1331":"1252–1331","–Male":"Surnud","–1354":"–1354","1281–1329":"1281–1329","1300":"1300","1354":"1354","1254":"1254","1331":"1331","1252":"1252","1281":"1281","1329":"1329","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Wester Powrie, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1254–1300":"1254–1300","1252–1331":"1252–1331","–Male":"Kuollut","–1354":"–1354","1281–1329":"1281–1329","1300":"1300","1354":"1354","1254":"1254","1331":"1331","1252":"1252","1281":"1281","1329":"1329","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wester Powrie, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1254–1300":"1254–1300","1252–1331":"1252–1331","–Male":"Décédé","–1354":"–1354","1281–1329":"1281–1329","1300":"1300","1354":"1354","1254":"1254","1331":"1331","1252":"1252","1281":"1281","1329":"1329","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Wester Powrie, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Écoss